race.comment: SAKER FALCON (6) lightly raced gelding mixing his distances up. Never comfortable in the heavy (9) going when a plugging fourth over 2000m at Wangaratta. Kept fresh and he finds a very weak Maiden. NOIR VITESSE (5) fitter after the two runs this time in and has a host of gear changes today. Finished third over 1800m at Hawkesbury last campaign. That form looks good enough to see him figure prominently. LORD LIMERICK (10) improving with racing and gives the indication he will relish this trip. Covered plenty of ground in the run when fifth over 1180m at Gundagai. Maps well and can take a hand in the finish. DOC MARCH (3) has not raced since finishing 1.4 lengths away in fourth over 2100m at Narrandera on July 13. In the mix fresh.
